@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Bloksters" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed. The only requirement is that your Workbench
must have at least 8 colours.

                             How to play?

  The play area, or 'arena', is a board of 9 by 9 spaces that
contains various coloured blocks. When blocks of the same colour are
located next to each other, these blocks get 'connected' by a small
link. Surrounding the arena is a border where the next block is
positioned.

  You can move a block anywhere on a border in the following ways:

  -By clicking anywhere on a border (except on the block itself),
   this will move the block at the position you clicked on.

  -By clicking in a triangular area that is located between a border
   and the small dots that form an 'X', the block will move in line
   from the position you clicked on.

  -By clicking on one of the small dots in the arena, depending on
   which border the block is located, the block will move in line
   from the clicked position, on the border it was originally
   located.

  Clicking on the border block will send it in the arena until it
touches another block already there. If there are no block in line
horizontally or vertically, the border block will not move. If the
block that was sent touches a block of the same colour, both will
be linked together, as well as to other neighbouring blocks of the
same colour.

  When 4 or more blocks of the same colour are lined-up, they will
'explode' and then will be removed from the arena. You get 1 point
for 4 blocks of the same colour, but 5 blocks give 5 points, 6
blocks give 25 points and 7 blocks give 125 points.

  The game ends when the arena is full or if it is impossible to add
a block, because all positions next to the borders are occupied.

  If you clear up the board, meaning that there are no remaining
blocks, the game will end, and your final score will be doubled.

  Have fun!

